## handoff
- produced: Full WordPress demo — 9 pages live on Surface:8081, mdr-theme (14 templates + CSS/JS), Rank Math SEO (all pages titled/described), LocalBusiness schema, before/after slider, sticky CTAs, pricing/gallery/FAQ/estimate forms, GA4 hooks; 2 admin logins; mdr-wordpress-docker service registered; bridge blueprint at mw-backend (not yet pushed)
- decisions: Canonical redirect disabled (`remove_filter('template_redirect','redirect_canonical')`) to break sub-path proxy loop; theme synced to host mount for restart durability; custom HTML forms used (not FF shortcodes) — sufficient for demo; static assets served directly by Apache without redirect
- next needs: deploy step — `git add maryland_driveway_wp_bridge_blueprint.py server.py && git commit && git push` in mw-backend; wait ~30s for Flask restart; verify `https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/` returns 200; michaelwegter.com push if any changes staged there
- risks: Public URL is 404 until bridge is pushed; if WP container stops, run-server.ps1 auto-restarts via services.json entry; AppFrame iframes cross-origin (michaelwegter.com → api.michaelwegter.com) — confirm AppFrame allows cross-origin src or add the domain to CSP
